colors.name: Gradient/skeuemorphic-gradient-border
colors.description: Used to create a subtle skeuemorphic effect in components such as primary buttons. This can be removed or replaced with a 1px stroke if you prefer a flat style.

Used to create a subtle skeuomorphic effect in components such as buttons and tabs.

This can be removed or replaced with shadow-xs if you prefer a flat style.

effectStyles.name: Focus rings/focus-ring
effectStyles.description: Used for focus states in components. For example toggles and checkboxes.

effectStyles.name: Focus rings/focus-ring-shadow-xs
effectStyles.description: Used for focus states in components that also require a shadow. For example, buttons and tabs.

effectStyles.name: Focus rings/focus-ring-shadow-xs-skeuomorphic
effectStyles.value: box-shadow: 0px 0px 0px 4px #3a97f7, 0px 0px 0px 2px #ffffff, 0px 1px 2px 0px rgba(10, 13, 18, 0.05), inset 0px -2px 0px 0px rgba(10, 13, 18, 0.05), inset 0px 0px 0px 1px rgba(10, 13, 18, 0.18)
effectStyles.description:
Used for focus states in components that also require a shadow and a subtle skeuomorphic effect. For example, buttons and tabs.

This can be replaced with focus-ring-shadow-xs if you prefer a flat style.

effectStyles.name: Focus rings/focus-ring-shadow-sm
effectStyles.description: Used for focus states in components that also require a shadow. For example, buttons and tabs.

effectStyles.name: Focus rings/focus-ring-error
effectStyles.description: Used for destructive or error focus states in components. For example, destructive button links.

effectStyles.name: Focus rings/focus-ring-error-shadow-xs
effectStyles.description: Used for destructive or error focus states in components that also require a shadow. For example, destructive buttons.

effectStyles.name: Focus rings/focus-ring-error-shadow-xs-skeuomorphic
effectStyles.value: box-shadow: 0px 0px 0px 4px #f04438, 0px 0px 0px 2px #ffffff, 0px 1px 2px 0px rgba(10, 13, 18, 0.05), inset 0px -2px 0px 0px rgba(10, 13, 18, 0.05), inset 0px 0px 0px 1px rgba(10, 13, 18, 0.18)
effectStyles.description:
Used for focus states in destructive or error components that also require a shadow and a subtle skeuomorphic effect. For example, destructive buttons.

This can be replaced with focus-ring-error-shadow-xs if you prefer a flat style.
